  h5.strong Stacked(Draw).

  p.slim About the same except each seed is suffled. You will still get 2 A players on a team, but a random draw. 


  br
  h5.strong Least Paired

  p.slim This method attempt to put players together that have not played together recently. The only difference between this method and others is that players are sorted by the number of 'interactions' they've had with others playing in the event. While this sounded like a neat concept, players A and B had not played together in a while, Players B and C may have played together 4 out the the last 6 Games! 

  br
  h5.strong Redistribution

  p.slim This method is about the same as least paired. In this case, the deck is sorted by how many PTPoints they've accumulated (money?)

  p.sllim.strong Both Redistributeion and Least Paired use the Stacked method to sort the teams. Players whose won the most or played the most will be teamed with players who won the least or played the least




